<div class='box2_7 floatl m brdr'>
 <h1>Regional</h1>
      <h2>Australia</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="http://www.astsports.com.au/cricket">Australian Sports Tours</a> -   Official tour operator of the Australian Cricket Board. Offers tours following   the team guided by legendary players. </li>
        <li><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/other_international/australia/default.stm" target="_blank">BBC Sport - Cricket: Australia</a> - Offers the latest scorecard and results plus fixtures, squad members and message board for fans. </li>
        <li><a href="http://www.cricket.com.au/">Cricket Australia</a> - All about   cricket in Australia including its history, the athletes, scholarships, coaches,   training and facilities including the Commonwealth Bank Cricket Academy. </li>
        <li><a href="http://sports.dir.groups.yahoo.com/dir/Recreation___Sports/Sports/Cricket/By_Location/Countries/Australia">Yahoo!   Sports Groups - Cricket: Australia</a> - Directory of cricket clubs and fan   groups which include message forums, chats, newsletters and photo galleries.</li>
      </ul>
       <h2>Bangladesh </h2>
          <ul>
        <li><a href="http://www.cricbd.com">CricBD</a> - Includes articles, player profiles and statistics, Test and ODI scorecards, message board, and news about the Tigers and the sport. Also provides a collection of essays and short stories and a book written by Omar Chowdhury. </li>
        <li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_World_Cup">Cricket World Cup</a> - Information about the biggest cricket event in the world. </li>
        <li><a href="http://www.banglacricket.com/">BlanglaCricket</a> - The official cricket site for Bangladesh Cricket fans. Come here for latest information on Bangladesh Cricket, live discussion, breaking news and much more. </li>
        <li><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/other_international/bangladesh/default.stm">BBC Sport - Cricket: Bangladesh</a> - Offers the latest scorecard and results plus fixtures, squad members and message board for fans. </li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Canada </h2>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="http://www.cricinfo.com/canada/content/team/17.html">Canadian Cricket Association</a> - Comprehensive site with indepth coverage of Canadian cricket. </li>
            <li><a href="http://www.bcmcl.org/">British Columbia Mainland Cricket League</a> - Features teams from the Greater Vancouver, Fraser Valley and Seattle areas.   Includes information about governing rules, playing fields, news, schedules,   standings, rosters and events. </li>
            <li><a href="http://www.canadacricket.com/">Canadacricket.com</a> - Online news   journal and information on cricket in Canada. </li>
            <li><a href="http://www.canadiancricket.org/">Canadian Cricket Association</a> -   The official voice of Canadian Cricket </li>
            <li><a href="http://www.cricket.mb.ca/">Manitoba Cricket Association</a> -   Organisation's executive committee, schedules, standings, and other information. </li>
            <li><a href="http://tcuandsa.homestead.com/Home.html">Toronto Cricket Umpires   and Scorers Association</a> - Information, news, umpiring and events. </li>
      </ul>
      <h2>England</h2>
      <ul>
                <li><a href="http://www.cricinfo.com/england/content/team/1.html">CricInfo -   England</a> - Live scores, news, features, player columns and profiles, audio   and video, shopping, statistical database and scorecard archive. </li>
                <li><a href="http://www.ecb.co.uk/">England and Wales Cricket Board</a> -   Coverage of domestic and international cricket. News, scores and statistics,   competitions, tickets, and merchandise. </li>
                <li><a href="http://www.lords.org/">Lord's</a> - ICC and ECB home of cricket at   Marylebone Cricket Club, founded in 1787. Includes news, virtual tour of the   Long Room, history and official laws of cricket, online shopping and ticket   sales.</li>
                </ul>
                  <h2>New Zealand</h2>
                <ul>
                <li><a href="http://www.acua.co.nz/">Auckland Cricket Umpires Association</a> -   Official site of association located in Auckland, New Zealand under the   direction of the Auckland Cricket Association (ACA). </li>
                <li><a href="http://www.bopcricket.co.nz/">Bay Of Plenty Cricket</a> - All about   cricket in the area including news, development programmes, clubs, tables and   photos. </li>
                <li><a href="http://www.cricinfo.com/newzealand/content/team/5.html">CricInfo -   New Zealand</a> - Details on international and domestic cricket, players,   statistics, grounds and general information. </li>
                <li><a href="http://www.blackcaps.co.nz/">Fun with Black Caps</a> -  Fansite dedicated to the New Zealand Cricket Team, including   original cricket photos, drawings, cartoons and &quot;encounters with black caps&quot;. </li>
                <li><a href="http://www.nationalbank.co.nz/about/cricket/">In the Field</a> -   Includes series previews, &quot;celebrity guest columns&quot;, player profiles, and former   Black Cap Gavin Larsen's column, provided by New Zealand cricket sponsor The   National Bank. </li>
                <li><a href="http://www.nzcricket.co.nz/">New Zealand Cricket</a> - Official   website. Includes news, schedules, and information about international, domestic   and women's cricket in New Zealand. </li>
                <li><a href="http://sports.groups.yahoo.com/group/nzcricket/">NZ Cricket Yahoo!   Group</a> - An email discussion list for all fans of the New Zealand Cricket   Team. </li>
                <li><a href="http://www.tvnz.co.nz/view/sport_sub_cat_skin/sport_cricket_index_group">NZOOM:   New Zealand Cricket</a> - Includes news and information on the New Zealand   Cricket team, previews, reviews, news and live-scoring for major international   cricket competitions. </li>
                <li><a href="http://www.onedayers.50megs.com/">PapaToeToe Oneday Fours</a> -   Includes a listing of players, photographs, news items, statistics, past season   coverage and a hall of fame section. </li>
                <li><a href="http://www.stuff.co.nz/stuff/0,2106,0a10133,00.html">STUFF: Sport:   Cricket</a> - Cricket news stories from New Zealand newspapers. </li>
                <li><a href="http://sports.dir.groups.yahoo.com/dir/Recreation___Sports/Sports/Cricket/By_Location/Countries/New_Zealand">Yahoo!   Sports Groups - Cricket: New Zealand</a> - Directory of cricket clubs and fan   groups which include message forums, chats, newsletters and photo galleries.</li>
                </ul>
    <h2>South Africa Cricket Links</h2>
                <ul>
                  <li><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/other_international/south_africa/" target="_blank">BBC Sport - Cricket: South Africa</a> - Offers the latest scorecard and results plus fixtures, squad members and message board for fans. </li>
                  <li><a href="http://www.futurecricket.co.za/" target="_blank">Future Cricket</a> - News and information about youth cricket including Western Cape school cricket rankings, player and team stats and profiles, fixtures, results and coaching tips.</li>
                  <li><a href="http://www.ucbsa.cricket.org/" target="_blank">United Cricket Board of South Africa (CBSA)</a> - Governing body provides live match score cards, pictures, live statistics, chat and match reports. </li>
                  <li><a href="http://dir.groups.yahoo.com/dir/Recreation___Sports/Sports/Cricket/By_Location/Countries/South_Africa" target="_blank">Yahoo! Sports Groups - Cricket: South Africa</a> - Directory of cricket clubs and fan groups which include message forums, chats, newsletters and photo galleries. </li>
                </ul>
